Main Tasks And Responsibilities

Noesis is looking for professionals with the following profile:


Analyze and document business requirements for BI projects, translating stakeholder needs into technical specifications;
Design and develop BI dimensional data models to support business intelligence solutions;
Conduct user acceptance testing (UAT) and perform data validation to ensure high data quality;
Provide training, documentation, and operational support to BI tool end-users.


Profile


Degree in Computer Science or similar;
Minimum of 3 years of experience in BI Functional Analysis or Data Analysis;
Strong proficiency in SQL and solid knowledge of BI modeling concepts, including dimensional modeling (Star Schema and Snowflake);
Solid capability to analyze and interpret data across both relational systems (source systems) and BI environments;
Excellent communication skills to bridge the gap effectively between technical teams and business areas;
Proactive and analytical mindset, with a strong ability to transform business requirements into technical mapping and ETL rules;


If you meet these requirements and are interested in joining an audacious and innovative company, please send us your application.

Join us. Let’s innovate together!

All our recruitment and selection processes are based on equal opportunities, valuing the competence and potential of each person and ensuring that no candidate is discriminated on the grounds of gender, ethnicity, sexual orientation, age, religion or physical condition.


